0.body: KAM is an institutional asset management protocol that implements a dual-track architecture for both institutional and retail access. The protocol creates kTokens (kUSD, kBTC) backed 1:1 by real assets (USDC, WBTC), providing institutions with direct minting and redemption capabilities while offering retail users yield opportunities through external strategy deployment. The system features batch processing with virtual balance accounting, two-phase settlement with timelock proposals, and modular vault architecture through diamond pattern implementation. For more information, refer to the architecture documentation .
